<domain>
(define (domain orchestration-domain)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types agent item location phase)

  (:predicates
    ;; Roles
    (role-observer ?a - agent)
    (role-executor ?a - agent)
    (role-auditor ?a - agent)

    ;; Positions
    (agent-at ?a - agent ?l - location)
    (item-at ?i - item ?l - location)

    ;; Item states
    (inventoried ?i - item)
    (processed ?i - item)
    (verified ?i - item)

    ;; Phases and ordering
    (phase ?p - phase)
    (current-phase ?p - phase)
    (next ?p - phase ?q - phase)
  )

  ;; Observer action: record an inventory entry for an item; only in phase p1
  (:action inventory-by-observer
    :parameters (?obs - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)
    :precondition (and
      (role-observer ?obs)
      (agent-at ?obs ?loc)
      (item-at ?it ?loc)
      (current-phase p1)
      (not (inventoried ?it))
    )
    :effect (and
      (inventoried ?it)
    )
  )

  ;; Executor action: process an inventoried item; only in phase p2
  (:action process-by-executor
    :parameters (?exe - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)
    :precondition (and
      (role-executor ?exe)
      (agent-at ?exe ?loc)
      (item-at ?it ?loc)
      (inventoried ?it)
      (current-phase p2)
      (not (processed ?it))
    )
    :effect (and
      (processed ?it)
    )
  )

  ;; Auditor action: verify a processed item; only in phase p3
  (:action verify-by-auditor
    :parameters (?aud - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)
    :precondition (and
      (role-auditor ?aud)
      (agent-at ?aud ?loc)
      (item-at ?it ?loc)
      (processed ?it)
      (current-phase p3)
      (not (verified ?it))
    )
    :effect (and
      (verified ?it)
    )
  )

  ;; Advance phase from p1 to p2: only allowed when all items are inventoried
  (:action advance-phase-1-to-2
    :parameters (?obs - agent)
    :precondition (and
      (role-observer ?obs)
      (current-phase p1)
      ;; hard constraints: every item must be inventoried before advancing
      (inventoried item1)
      (inventoried item2)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-phase p1))
      (current-phase p2)
    )
  )

  ;; Advance phase from p2 to p3: only allowed when all items are processed
  (:action advance-phase-2-to-3
    :parameters (?obs - agent)
    :precondition (and
      (role-observer ?obs)
      (current-phase p2)
      ;; hard constraints: every item must be processed before advancing
      (processed item1)
      (processed item2)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-phase p2))
      (current-phase p3)
    )
  )

  ;; (Optional) A single action to move an agent between locations if needed.
  ;; Movement is allowed at any phase but is explicit so agents must be at the item location to act.
  (:action move-agent
    :parameters (?a - agent ?from - location ?to - location)
    :precondition (and
      (agent-at ?a ?from)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (agent-at ?a ?from))
      (agent-at ?a ?to)
    )
  )

)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem orchestration-problem)
  (:domain orchestration-domain)

  (:objects
    ;; Agents
    observer1 executor1 auditor1 - agent

    ;; Items to be inventoried, processed, and audited
    item1 item2 - item

    ;; Locations (all placed at the same location for simplicity; movement allowed)
    storage - location

    ;; Phases (explicit time slots)
    p1 p2 p3 - phase
  )

  (:init
    ;; Roles
    (role-observer observer1)
    (role-executor executor1)
    (role-auditor auditor1)

    ;; Agent locations
    (agent-at observer1 storage)
    (agent-at executor1 storage)
    (agent-at auditor1 storage)

    ;; Item locations
    (item-at item1 storage)
    (item-at item2 storage)

    ;; Phase structure and starting phase
    (phase p1)
    (phase p2)
    (phase p3)
    (next p1 p2)
    (next p2 p3)
    (current-phase p1)

    ;; No items are inventoried, processed, or verified at start
    ;; (inventoried item1) absent
    ;; (processed item1) absent
    ;; (verified item1) absent
    ;; same for item2
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; Auditor report mandates every item must be verified and the process must be in final phase p3
      (verified item1)
      (verified item2)
      (current-phase p3)
    )
  )
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain orchestration-domain)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types agent item location phase)

  (:predicates
    ;; Roles
    (role-observer ?a - agent)
    (role-executor ?a - agent)
    (role-auditor ?a - agent)

    ;; Positions
    (agent-at ?a - agent ?l - location)
    (item-at ?i - item ?l - location)

    ;; Item states
    (inventoried ?i - item)
    (processed ?i - item)
    (verified ?i - item)

    ;; Phases and ordering
    (phase ?p - phase)
    (current-phase ?p - phase)
    (next ?p - phase ?q - phase)
  )

  ;; Observer action: record an inventory entry for an item; only in phase p1
  (:action inventory-by-observer
    :parameters (?obs - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)
    :precondition (and
      (role-observer ?obs)
      (agent-at ?obs ?loc)
      (item-at ?it ?loc)
      (current-phase p1)
      (not (inventoried ?it))
    )
    :effect (and
      (inventoried ?it)
    )
  )

  ;; Executor action: process an inventoried item; only in phase p2
  (:action process-by-executor
    :parameters (?exe - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)
    :precondition (and
      (role-executor ?exe)
      (agent-at ?exe ?loc)
      (item-at ?it ?loc)
      (inventoried ?it)
      (current-phase p2)
      (not (processed ?it))
    )
    :effect (and
      (processed ?it)
    )
  )

  ;; Auditor action: verify a processed item; only in phase p3
  (:action verify-by-auditor
    :parameters (?aud - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)
    :precondition (and
      (role-auditor ?aud)
      (agent-at ?aud ?loc)
      (item-at ?it ?loc)
      (processed ?it)
      (current-phase p3)
      (not (verified ?it))
    )
    :effect (and
      (verified ?it)
    )
  )

  ;; Advance phase from p1 to p2: only allowed when all items are inventoried
  (:action advance-phase-1-to-2
    :parameters (?obs - agent)
    :precondition (and
      (role-observer ?obs)
      (current-phase p1)
      ;; hard constraints: every item must be inventoried before advancing
      (inventoried item1)
      (inventoried item2)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-phase p1))
      (current-phase p2)
    )
  )

  ;; Advance phase from p2 to p3: only allowed when all items are processed
  (:action advance-phase-2-to-3
    :parameters (?obs - agent)
    :precondition (and
      (role-observer ?obs)
      (current-phase p2)
      ;; hard constraints: every item must be processed before advancing
      (processed item1)
      (processed item2)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-phase p2))
      (current-phase p3)
    )
  )

  ;; (Optional) A single action to move an agent between locations if needed.
  ;; Movement is allowed at any phase but is explicit so agents must be at the item location to act.
  (:action move-agent
    :parameters (?a - agent ?from - location ?to - location)
    :precondition (and
      (agent-at ?a ?from)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (agent-at ?a ?from))
      (agent-at ?a ?to)
    )
  )

)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem orchestration-problem)
  (:domain orchestration-domain)

  (:objects
    ;; Agents
    observer1 executor1 auditor1 - agent

    ;; Items to be inventoried, processed, and audited
    item1 item2 - item

    ;; Locations (all placed at the same location for simplicity; movement allowed)
    storage - location

    ;; Phases (explicit time slots)
    p1 p2 p3 - phase
  )

  (:init
    ;; Roles
    (role-observer observer1)
    (role-executor executor1)
    (role-auditor auditor1)

    ;; Agent locations
    (agent-at observer1 storage)
    (agent-at executor1 storage)
    (agent-at auditor1 storage)

    ;; Item locations
    (item-at item1 storage)
    (item-at item2 storage)

    ;; Phase structure and starting phase
    (phase p1)
    (phase p2)
    (phase p3)
    (next p1 p2)
    (next p2 p3)
    (current-phase p1)

    ;; No items are inventoried, processed, or verified at start
    ;; (inventoried item1) absent
    ;; (processed item1) absent
    ;; (verified item1) absent
    ;; same for item2
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; Auditor report mandates every item must be verified and the process must be in final phase p3
      (verified item1)
      (verified item2)
      (current-phase p3)
    )
  )
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain orchestration-domain)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types agent item location phase)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; Roles\n    (role-observer ?a - agent)\n    (role-executor ?a - agent)\n    (role-auditor ?a - agent)\n\n    ;; Positions\n    (agent-at ?a - agent ?l - location)\n    (item-at ?i - item ?l - location)\n\n    ;; Item states\n    (inventoried ?i - item)\n    (processed ?i - item)\n    (verified ?i - item)\n\n    ;; Phases and ordering\n    (phase ?p - phase)\n    (current-phase ?p - phase)\n    (next ?p - phase ?q - phase)\n  )\n\n  ;; Observer action: record an inventory entry for an item; only in phase p1\n  (:action inventory-by-observer\n    :parameters (?obs - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)\n    :precondition (and\n      (role-observer ?obs)\n      (agent-at ?obs ?loc)\n      (item-at ?it ?loc)\n      (current-phase p1)\n      (not (inventoried ?it))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (inventoried ?it)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Executor action: process an inventoried item; only in phase p2\n  (:action process-by-executor\n    :parameters (?exe - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)\n    :precondition (and\n      (role-executor ?exe)\n      (agent-at ?exe ?loc)\n      (item-at ?it ?loc)\n      (inventoried ?it)\n      (current-phase p2)\n      (not (processed ?it))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (processed ?it)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Auditor action: verify a processed item; only in phase p3\n  (:action verify-by-auditor\n    :parameters (?aud - agent ?it - item ?loc - location)\n    :precondition (and\n      (role-auditor ?aud)\n      (agent-at ?aud ?loc)\n      (item-at ?it ?loc)\n      (processed ?it)\n      (current-phase p3)\n      (not (verified ?it))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (verified ?it)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Advance phase from p1 to p2: only allowed when all items are inventoried\n  (:action advance-phase-1-to-2\n    :parameters (?obs - agent)\n    :precondition (and\n      (role-observer ?obs)\n      (current-phase p1)\n      ;; hard constraints: every item must be inventoried before advancing\n      (inventoried item1)\n      (inventoried item2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-phase p1))\n      (current-phase p2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Advance phase from p2 to p3: only allowed when all items are processed\n  (:action advance-phase-2-to-3\n    :parameters (?obs - agent)\n    :precondition (and\n      (role-observer ?obs)\n      (current-phase p2)\n      ;; hard constraints: every item must be processed before advancing\n      (processed item1)\n      (processed item2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-phase p2))\n      (current-phase p3)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; (Optional) A single action to move an agent between locations if needed.\n  ;; Movement is allowed at any phase but is explicit so agents must be at the item location to act.\n  (:action move-agent\n    :parameters (?a - agent ?from - location ?to - location)\n    :precondition (and\n      (agent-at ?a ?from)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (agent-at ?a ?from))\n      (agent-at ?a ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem orchestration-problem)\n  (:domain orchestration-domain)\n\n  (:objects\n    ;; Agents\n    observer1 executor1 auditor1 - agent\n\n    ;; Items to be inventoried, processed, and audited\n    item1 item2 - item\n\n    ;; Locations (all placed at the same location for simplicity; movement allowed)\n    storage - location\n\n    ;; Phases (explicit time slots)\n    p1 p2 p3 - phase\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; Roles\n    (role-observer observer1)\n    (role-executor executor1)\n    (role-auditor auditor1)\n\n    ;; Agent locations\n    (agent-at observer1 storage)\n    (agent-at executor1 storage)\n    (agent-at auditor1 storage)\n\n    ;; Item locations\n    (item-at item1 storage)\n    (item-at item2 storage)\n\n    ;; Phase structure and starting phase\n    (phase p1)\n    (phase p2)\n    (phase p3)\n    (next p1 p2)\n    (next p2 p3)\n    (current-phase p1)\n\n    ;; No items are inventoried, processed, or verified at start\n    ;; (inventoried item1) absent\n    ;; (processed item1) absent\n    ;; (verified item1) absent\n    ;; same for item2\n  )\n\n  (:goal\n    (and\n      ;; Auditor report mandates every item must be verified and the process must be in final phase p3\n      (verified item1)\n      (verified item2)\n      (current-phase p3)\n    )\n  )\n)",

obj)\n    (texture ?x - obj)\n    (vase ?x - obj ?y - obj)\n    (next ?x - obj ?y - obj)\n    (sneeze ?x - obj)\n    (collect ?x - obj ?y - obj)\n    (spring ?x - obj)\n    (stupendous ?x - obj)\n    ;; explicit discrete stage progression to enforce ordered action application\n    (current ?s - FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain orchestrator-domain)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types agent player recorder auditor item place phase)

  ; Predicates
  (:predicates
    (at ?a - agent ?p - place)
    (item-at ?i - item ?p - place)
    (holding ?a - agent ?i - item)
    (processed ?i - item)
    (recorded ?i - item)
    (archived ?i - item)
    (verified ?i - item)
    (phase-active ?ph - phase)
    (phase-next ?ph1 - phase ?ph2 - phase)
    (phase-complete ?ph - phase)
    (finalized)
  )

  ; Generic movement for any agent (player, recorder, auditor)
  (:action move
    :parameters (?a - agent ?from - place ?to - place)
    :precondition (and (at ?a ?from) (not (at ?a ?to)))
    :effect (and (at ?a ?to) (not (at ?a ?from)))
  )

  ; paltry: player_agent picks up an item during the first phase; activates next phase.
  (:action paltry
    :parameters (?p - player ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase ?next - phase)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?p ?loc)
        (item-at ?it ?loc)
        (phase-active ?ph)
        (phase-next ?ph ?next)
        (not (holding ?p ?it))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (holding ?p ?it)
        (not (item-at ?it ?loc))
        (not (phase-active ?ph))
        (phase-complete ?ph)
        (phase-active ?next)
      )
  )

  ; sip: player_agent processes the held item during the second phase; places it at the processing place and advances phase.
  (:action sip
    :parameters (?p - player ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase ?next - phase)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?p ?loc)
        (holding ?p ?it)
        (phase-active ?ph)
        (phase-next ?ph ?next)
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (not (holding ?p ?it))
        (item-at ?it ?loc)
        (processed ?it)
        (not (phase-active ?ph))
        (phase-complete ?ph)
        (phase-active ?next)
      )
  )

  ; clip: recorder_agent creates a record of a processed item while the final phase is active (no phase transition here).
  (:action clip
    :parameters (?r - recorder ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?r ?loc)
        (item-at ?it ?loc)
        (processed ?it)
        (phase-active ?ph)
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (recorded ?it)
      )
  )

  ; wretched: recorder_agent archives a previously recorded item; requires recorder at archive location.
  (:action wretched
    :parameters (?r - recorder ?it - item ?loc - place)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?r ?loc)
        (recorded ?it)
        (not (archived ?it))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (archived ?it)
      )
  )

  ; memory: auditor_agent verifies that an archived item is correctly archived.
  (:action memory
    :parameters (?o - auditor ?it - item ?loc - place)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?o ?loc)
        (archived ?it)
        (not (verified ?it))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (verified ?it)
      )
  )

  ; tightfisted: auditor_agent finalizes the workflow once all terminal conditions hold and agents are in their final positions.
  ; This action enforces the finalization as an explicit step and therefore encodes ordering (it must be the last step).
  (:action tightfisted
    :parameters (?o - auditor ?p - player ?r - recorder ?locP - place ?locR - place ?locO - place ?it - item)
    :precondition
      (and
        (verified ?it)
        (processed ?it)
        (archived ?it)
        (at ?p ?locP)
        (at ?r ?locR)
        (at ?o ?locO)
        (not (finalized))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (finalized)
      )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem orchestrator-problem)
  (:domain orchestrator-domain)

  (:objects
    ; agents (typed)
    player1 - player
    recorder1 - recorder
    auditor1 - auditor

    ; items
    itemA - item

    ; places
    office lab archive - place

    ; phases
    p1 p2 p3 - phase
  )

  (:init
    ; initial agent locations
    (at player1 office)
    (at recorder1 lab)
    (at auditor1 archive)

    ; initial item location
    (item-at itemA office)

    ; phase order and initial active phase
    (phase-next p1 p2)
    (phase-next p2 p3)
    (phase-active p1)

    ; No other fluents hold initially: not processed, not recorded, not archived, not verified, not finalized
  )

  ; Goal: enforce all mandated terminal conditions explicitly.
  (:goal
    (and
      (processed itemA)
      (archived itemA)
      (verified itemA)
      ; final agent positions required by the specification:
      (at player1 lab)
      (at recorder1 archive)
      (at auditor1 archive)
      ; final explicit finalization step (ensures ordering)
      (finalized)
    )
  )
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain orchestrator-domain)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types agent player recorder auditor item place phase)

  ; Predicates
  (:predicates
    (at ?a - agent ?p - place)
    (item-at ?i - item ?p - place)
    (holding ?a - agent ?i - item)
    (processed ?i - item)
    (recorded ?i - item)
    (archived ?i - item)
    (verified ?i - item)
    (phase-active ?ph - phase)
    (phase-next ?ph1 - phase ?ph2 - phase)
    (phase-complete ?ph - phase)
    (finalized)
  )

  ; Generic movement for any agent (player, recorder, auditor)
  (:action move
    :parameters (?a - agent ?from - place ?to - place)
    :precondition (and (at ?a ?from) (not (at ?a ?to)))
    :effect (and (at ?a ?to) (not (at ?a ?from)))
  )

  ; paltry: player_agent picks up an item during the first phase; activates next phase.
  (:action paltry
    :parameters (?p - player ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase ?next - phase)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?p ?loc)
        (item-at ?it ?loc)
        (phase-active ?ph)
        (phase-next ?ph ?next)
        (not (holding ?p ?it))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (holding ?p ?it)
        (not (item-at ?it ?loc))
        (not (phase-active ?ph))
        (phase-complete ?ph)
        (phase-active ?next)
      )
  )

  ; sip: player_agent processes the held item during the second phase; places it at the processing place and advances phase.
  (:action sip
    :parameters (?p - player ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase ?next - phase)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?p ?loc)
        (holding ?p ?it)
        (phase-active ?ph)
        (phase-next ?ph ?next)
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (not (holding ?p ?it))
        (item-at ?it ?loc)
        (processed ?it)
        (not (phase-active ?ph))
        (phase-complete ?ph)
        (phase-active ?next)
      )
  )

  ; clip: recorder_agent creates a record of a processed item while the final phase is active (no phase transition here).
  (:action clip
    :parameters (?r - recorder ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?r ?loc)
        (item-at ?it ?loc)
        (processed ?it)
        (phase-active ?ph)
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (recorded ?it)
      )
  )

  ; wretched: recorder_agent archives a previously recorded item; requires recorder at archive location.
  (:action wretched
    :parameters (?r - recorder ?it - item ?loc - place)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?r ?loc)
        (recorded ?it)
        (not (archived ?it))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (archived ?it)
      )
  )

  ; memory: auditor_agent verifies that an archived item is correctly archived.
  (:action memory
    :parameters (?o - auditor ?it - item ?loc - place)
    :precondition
      (and
        (at ?o ?loc)
        (archived ?it)
        (not (verified ?it))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (verified ?it)
      )
  )

  ; tightfisted: auditor_agent finalizes the workflow once all terminal conditions hold and agents are in their final positions.
  ; This action enforces the finalization as an explicit step and therefore encodes ordering (it must be the last step).
  (:action tightfisted
    :parameters (?o - auditor ?p - player ?r - recorder ?locP - place ?locR - place ?locO - place ?it - item)
    :precondition
      (and
        (verified ?it)
        (processed ?it)
        (archived ?it)
        (at ?p ?locP)
        (at ?r ?locR)
        (at ?o ?locO)
        (not (finalized))
      )
    :effect
      (and
        (finalized)
      )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem orchestrator-problem)
  (:domain orchestrator-domain)

  (:objects
    ; agents (typed)
    player1 - player
    recorder1 - recorder
    auditor1 - auditor

    ; items
    itemA - item

    ; places
    office lab archive - place

    ; phases
    p1 p2 p3 - phase
  )

  (:init
    ; initial agent locations
    (at player1 office)
    (at recorder1 lab)
    (at auditor1 archive)

    ; initial item location
    (item-at itemA office)

    ; phase order and initial active phase
    (phase-next p1 p2)
    (phase-next p2 p3)
    (phase-active p1)

    ; No other fluents hold initially: not processed, not recorded, not archived, not verified, not finalized
  )

  ; Goal: enforce all mandated terminal conditions explicitly.
  (:goal
    (and
      (processed itemA)
      (archived itemA)
      (verified itemA)
      ; final agent positions required by the specification:
      (at player1 lab)
      (at recorder1 archive)
      (at auditor1 archive)
      ; final explicit finalization step (ensures ordering)
      (finalized)
    )
  )
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain orchestrator-domain)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types agent player recorder auditor item place phase)\n\n  ; Predicates\n  (:predicates\n    (at ?a - agent ?p - place)\n    (item-at ?i - item ?p - place)\n    (holding ?a - agent ?i - item)\n    (processed ?i - item)\n    (recorded ?i - item)\n    (archived ?i - item)\n    (verified ?i - item)\n    (phase-active ?ph - phase)\n    (phase-next ?ph1 - phase ?ph2 - phase)\n    (phase-complete ?ph - phase)\n    (finalized)\n  )\n\n  ; sip: player_agent processes the held item during the second phase; places it at the processing place and advances phase.\n  (:action sip\n    :parameters (?p - player ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase ?next - phase)\n    :precondition\n      (and\n        (at ?p ?loc)\n        (holding ?p ?it)\n        (phase-active ?ph)\n        (phase-next ?ph ?next)\n      )\n    :effect\n      (and\n        (not (holding ?p ?it))\n        (item-at ?it ?loc)\n        (processed ?it)\n        (not (phase-active ?ph))\n        (phase-complete ?ph)\n        (phase-active ?next)\n      )\n  )\n\n  ; clip: recorder_agent creates a record of a processed item while the final phase is active (no phase transition here).\n  (:action clip\n    :parameters (?r - recorder ?it - item ?loc - place ?ph - phase)\n    :precondition\n      (and\n        (at ?r ?loc)\n        (item-at ?it ?loc)\n        (processed ?it)\n        (phase-active ?ph)\n      )\n    :effect\n      (and\n        (recorded ?it)\n      )\n  )\n\n  ; wretched: recorder_agent archives a previously recorded item; requires recorder at archive location.\n  (:action wretched\n    :parameters (?r - recorder ?it - item ?loc - place)\n    :precondition\n      (and\n        (at ?r ?loc)\n        (recorded ?it)\n        (not (archived ?it))\n      )\n    :effect\n      (and\n        (archived ?it)\n      )\n  )\n\n  ; tightfisted: auditor_agent finalizes the workflow once all terminal conditions hold and agents are in their final positions.\n  ; This action enforces the finalization as an explicit step and therefore encodes ordering (it must be the last step).\n  (:action tightfisted\n    :parameters (?o - auditor ?p - player ?r - recorder ?locP - place ?locR - place ?locO - place ?it - item)\n    :precondition\n      (and\n        (verified ?it)\n        (processed ?it)\n        (archived ?it)\n        (at ?p ?locP)\n        (at ?r ?locR)\n        (at ?o ?locO)\n        (not (finalized))\n      )\n    :effect\n      (and\n        (finalized)\n      )\n  )\n)",
